		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We consider the problem of optimizing convex and concave functions with access to an erroneous zeroth-order oracle. In particular, for a given function x → f (x) we consider optimization when one is given access to absolute error oracles that return values in [f (x) − , f (x) + ] or relative error oracles that return value in [(1 −)f (x), (1 +)f (x)], for some &gt; 0. We show stark information theoretic impossibility results for minimizing convex functions and maximizing concave functions over polytopes in this model.</p>
			</abstract>
